The term wetlands describes marshes , swamps , bogs and similar areas usually situated between dry land and bodies of water .
They play important roles in filtering and cleansing water , preventing soil erosion , preventing soil and water pollution , serving as a reservoir for flood waters and in harboring fish , shellfish , wild plants , migratory birds , waterfowl and tiny organisms essential to the food chain .
Wetlands , so important to humans as well as wildlife , are endangered by human draining and development in many parts of the world .
The demand for more farmland , roads , houses and commercial or industrial development leads to destruction of wetlands .
More than half of the wetlands in the U.S. have been lost since the late s .
