In at a follow up Ramsar Convention conference delegates from countries launched the Wetlands International .
Active programs to protect wetlands are underway in countries as varied as China , Vietnam , India , Uganda and the United States .
In the U.S. early efforts of the Environmental Protection Agency and environmental groups were thwarted by the Army Corps of Engineers which was more compliant to the wishes of builders than to environmental regulations .
